      "label": "That's not a node editor.  That is a new medium",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "--- name: many-claudes-disambiguate description: \"The user",
      "uuid": "dbd235f502c0487488211c459e8a2efa",
      "x": -1620.2738877070478,
      "y": 1733.296414751736,
      "width": 593.0,
      "height": 161.0,
      "z_value": -9.92800000000004,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "  Runs several distinct Claude implementations, (almost) all just named \\\"Claude\\\" \u2014 when a request says \\\"Claude\\\"/\\\"the proofreader\\\"/\\\"ClaudeNode\\\", confirm WHICH one before acting\" metadata: node_type: memory type: user originSessionId: 85bb8623-2c0a-4983-8613-5c167d7def0d hook: | - [Many Claudes \u2014 check which one](user_many_claudes_disambiguate.md) \u2014 several distinct Claudes, nearly all named \"Claude\"; confirm which is meant before acting ---"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "The user runs several distinct Claude implementations",
      "uuid": "a74fbf6b11b241849a962450bdaa4caa",
      "x": -1704.340177205188,
      "y": 1515.064408618291,
      "width": 545.0,
      "height": 131.0,
      "z_value": -9.92700000000004,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "  And by deliberate naming convention they are (almost) all just called \"Claude\" \u2014 so terminology collisions are routine, not sloppiness. When a request names \"Claude\", \"the proofreader\", \"ClaudeNode\", etc., and more than one could fit, confirm WHICH one is meant before acting."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "> \"the most productive kitchen in the world is catching up",
      "uuid": "30e50558ef5144dfa082305f5069227d",
      "x": -513.5329434770294,
      "y": 2512.3725290862894,
      "width": 592.0,
      "height": 101.0,
      "z_value": -9.913000000000048,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "  To all the orders, we need to go faster\""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Delicate",
      "uuid": "9617ed795c6f4f668807eb9badab1e39",
      "x": 6625.52776701575,
      "y": 3404.739045464637,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 116.0,
      "z_value": -9.971000000000016,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Text encoding: to generate videos you must configure text encoding:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Practical and pleasurable",
      "uuid": "f6b5030ab894417f8001cc28d44e45fe",
      "x": 6469.3805826850385,
      "y": 4107.430195809584,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 251.0,
      "z_value": -9.970000000000017,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "- **LTX API key** (cloud text encoding) \u2014 **text encoding via the API is completely FREE** and highly recommended to speed up inference and save memory. Generate a free API key at the [LTX Console](https://console.ltx.video/). [Read more](https://ltx.io/model/model-blog/ltx-2-better-control-for-real-workflows).\n- **Local Text Encoder** (extra download; enables fully-local operation on supported Windows hardware) \u2014 if you don't wish to generate an API key, you can encode text locally via the settings menu."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Sweet",
      "uuid": "e08d161510e047078c6639a386064287",
      "x": 6270.564988157874,
      "y": 3220.732740229095,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 131.0,
      "z_value": -9.972000000000016,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "On first launch you may be prompted to review/accept model license terms (license text is fetched from Hugging Face; requires internet)."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Accurate",
      "uuid": "bd23f10f2d3b4111ae4800b056369433",
      "x": 6950.923668152818,
      "y": 4312.849529347785,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 101.0,
      "z_value": -9.969000000000017,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "## API keys, cost, and privacy"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Golden Hour",
      "uuid": "2b9fe4fe60864d049196aff9e7ad0445",
      "x": 1678.4552889138918,
      "y": 1138.2582300518545,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 146.0,
      "z_value": -9.995000000000003,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "LTX Desktop is an open-source desktop app for generating videos with LTX models \u2014 locally on supported Windows/Linux NVIDIA GPUs, with an API mode for unsupported hardware and macOS."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Distinct ones surfaced so far: - ClaudeNode: the",
      "uuid": "5da29630c9144c069c52aec9c9176843",
      "x": -778.3437680944924,
      "y": 1791.8313882378654,
      "width": 497.0,
      "height": 176.0,
      "z_value": -9.926000000000041,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "  In-Intricate, sidebar-loadable node; a file-parser over the local .claude transcripts (see [[claudenode-is-file-parser]]). Not an API chat. - The proofreader \u2014 a separate Claude implementation for writing analysis (rules in shared_braincell). It IS a core feature of The Majestic (which is part of Intricate) \u2014 do NOT treat it as isolated-from-Intricate; that framing was an earlier misread. - Sakura Claude \u2014 at least this one carries a distinguishing name. - ...and more; assume the roster grows."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "image",
      "title": "Image",
      "uuid": "d2759a3e3b7a434ca41af41ea7e3c63d",
      "x": 2049.235294117647,
      "y": -263.62250560524984,
      "width": 120.0,
      "height": 229.0,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "image_b64": "",
      "cache_key": "f7c038d68bd711255cf8ee823d69c77aac5310845498a5e0503af925cec47034",
      "caption": "Woman silhouette with heart shape",
      "source_path": "C:\\Users\\thisg\\Desktop\\A Charm in the shape of an Expressed Emotion\\Images\\downloadedImage (1).png",
      "source_size": 214207,
      "source_mtime": 1771066247.9638052,
      "show_border": true,
      "depth_front": false
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Why (the user, June 24th 2026)",
      "uuid": "9da7d4dad0ac441187071d271203aeea",
      "x": -932.666512320045,
      "y": 1507.5150596345331,
      "width": 321.0,
      "height": 221.0,
      "z_value": -9.925000000000042,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "  A deliberate life-approach, not laziness \u2014 every Claude is\nnamed Claude, every Arduino is named Lily ([[arduinos-named-lily]]), and the user\nrefers to multiple real brothers as \"my brother\" (singular) and any ex as \"my ex\": drawing\nthe distinction feels rude. Same convention across software, hardware, and life. See\n[[naming-as-memory-system]]."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Endless Potential",
      "uuid": "6c758e51f28f415aaab29e2f4df1832a",
      "x": 7650.954172668716,
      "y": 4558.863566449706,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 101.0,
      "z_value": -9.967000000000018,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The LTX API is used for:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Becoming Yours",
      "uuid": "1c9bf303cca94f6ba76ecdd547c350f9",
      "x": 7913.6723717006935,
      "y": 4225.353725954641,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 176.0,
      "z_value": -9.966000000000019,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "- **Cloud text encoding and prompt enhancement** \u2014 **FREE**; text encoding is highly recommended to speed up inference and save memory\n- API-based video generations (required on macOS and on unsupported Windows hardware) \u2014 paid\n- Retake \u2014 paid"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Elegant",
      "uuid": "e2154536ca1b4a82950f1f097e889eab",
      "x": 1466.802210956204,
      "y": 888.1564149005349,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 176.0,
      "z_value": -9.989000000000006,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "- Text-to-video generation\n- Image-to-video generation\n- Audio-to-video generation\n- Video edit generation (Retake)\n- Video Editor Interface\n- Video Editing Projects"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Becoming Yours",
      "uuid": "42c01d506845493e921e1e77387ae35a",
      "x": 7919.837484094808,
      "y": 3966.09380989531,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 161.0,
      "z_value": -9.96400000000002,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Generate a FREE API key at the [LTX Console](https://console.ltx.video/). Text encoding is free; video generation API usage is paid. [Read more](https://ltx.io/model/model-blog/ltx-2-better-control-for-real-workflows)."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Intricate",
      "uuid": "df414c2b279f4d7589a2593a3d10c1c9",
      "x": 7449.856824123644,
      "y": 4001.9358453842187,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 131.0,
      "z_value": -9.96500000000002,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "An LTX API key is required in API-only mode, but optional on Windows/Linux local mode if you enable the Local Text Encoder."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "All Glory",
      "uuid": "6235c84db4c54d79849cc2ab27e52086",
      "x": 2725.7395218413817,
      "y": 1049.3934074461533,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 116.0,
      "z_value": -9.986000000000008,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "In API-only mode, available resolutions/durations may be limited to what the API supports."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Evolve",
      "uuid": "a160c3cb1bfd40aeb4ff33dbc67b47d1",
      "x": 4995.961339941299,
      "y": 2189.2214261731933,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 116.0,
      "z_value": -9.975000000000014,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "LTX Desktop stores app data (settings, models, logs) in:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Delicate",
      "uuid": "092aef0d61bc4810a950c69e2ec6a870",
      "x": 6082.416292724712,
      "y": 3005.311794839173,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 116.0,
      "z_value": -9.973000000000015,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Model weights are downloaded into the `models/` subfolder (this can be large and may take time)."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Sweet",
      "uuid": "9c08bdc5621f4b94a140fdb686c96f03",
      "x": 2179.0417672045814,
      "y": 1006.6973132090097,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 101.0,
      "z_value": -9.988000000000007,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "## Local vs API mode"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "e8754270dbd94d68a4b48301a62c2417",
      "x": -999999.0,
      "y": -999999.0,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 316.0,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "Good \u2014 `source_path` is the right persistent identifier. Now I need to:\n\n1. Save `preview_pinned` and `preview_pinned_path` when pin state changes\n2. On session load, find the matching `ImageNode` and restore the pin",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
