    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "--- name: curator-low-zoom-recognition description: Why",
      "uuid": "ef05f78c90084f80936c9820a93476be",
      "x": -1902.538268731886,
      "y": 2552.4300042375676,
      "width": 565.0,
      "height": 206.0,
      "z_value": -9.923000000000043,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "  Intricate downsamples node content even at 4x4 px \u2014 the curator-as-viewer reads colour signatures of nodes they placed; content fidelity is not the goal at aerial view type: project originSessionId: 859c57a8-215d-4d36-aea8-66cb75fdf412 hook: | - [Curator recognition at low zoom](project_curator_low_zoom_recognition.md) \u2014 at 4\u00d74px the placer reads colour signatures; downsampling is a feature, not degradation --- At low zoom (down to ~4x4 px per node), Intricate keeps rendering downsampled node content rather than swapping in generic placeholders. The user navigates by colour/silhouette signature (\"the pink one\", \"the beige one\") because they placed the node there themselves."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "How to apply",
      "uuid": "0a6d5a024f4b4607bb25e9baf23068db",
      "x": -231.18719212962844,
      "y": 1770.2868897830406,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 146.0,
      "z_value": -9.924000000000042,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "  When a \"Claude\" reference is ambiguous, a quick \"which Claude?\" beats\nacting on the wrong one. Don't resolve it by assumption."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "How to apply",
      "uuid": "a79ae447dfde42d083fdcdb643cab5e9",
      "x": -1540.6961019150524,
      "y": 2251.971622642637,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 251.0,
      "z_value": -9.921000000000044,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "  When tempted to drop visual content at small zoom in favour of placeholders or generic markers, don't. Aerial-view downsampling is the feature, not degradation \u2014 it's how 1000+ node canvases stay navigable. Applies to future LOD decisions: preserve colour/shape signatures over content detail. Sibling frames: visual analogue of the cow principle (output reflects placer's input shape), sharper edge of gallery-not-trench and spatial-DAW. Distinct from pulse-vibrance \u2014 that is about always-on liveliness; this is about identity-through-signature regardless of zoom."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "--- name: kitchen-catching-up description: When the working",
      "uuid": "17cc871145ee421c82e682eff7a3ed62",
      "x": -2286.6691348602553,
      "y": 3373.456965358083,
      "width": 603.0,
      "height": 176.0,
      "z_value": -9.920000000000044,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Tools get faster (Opus model upgrades, infrastructure improvements), the user's response is to recalibrate ambition upward \u2014 not to coast at the previous pace. The focal list staying full is a calibration signal; an empty list means ambition needs raising, not that work caught up. type: feedback originSessionId: 577b2536-b9fa-42af-b76a-e1c926697add hook: | - [Tool capability \u2192 ambition](feedback_kitchen_catching_up.md) \u2014 upgrades raise ambition, not lower load; empty focal list = recalibration not victory --- User's articulation, 2026-05-02 (round 4):"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Why",
      "uuid": "01f868b956474041b3438f0cdcddd2cf",
      "x": -1944.4980627593268,
      "y": 2254.7861542430574,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 236.0,
      "z_value": -9.922000000000043,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "  This inverts the general-purpose assumption (Windows Explorer at small-icon view, generic image viewers, etc.) that small thumbnails are unreadable noise. That assumption holds when the viewer did not place the files. In Intricate the curator IS the viewer \u2014 silhouette + colour carries identity even when individual content is illegible. User said it verbatim on 2026-05-06: \"it always reads fine given the person on this side is the one that put them there in the first place.\""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "> \"in the first day of testing Opus 4.7 [...] our workflow",
      "uuid": "e4e2d052d7bc4349978843261d677727",
      "x": -1561.930156137329,
      "y": 3498.0258570495967,
      "width": 594.0,
      "height": 146.0,
      "z_value": -9.918000000000045,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "  Changed drastically between Opus 4.6 and 4.7, the moment 4.7 showed up, it caught up with the flow and the entire list emptied two times in the same day, hence the 'I had to go into the actual backlog', and recalibrate how we can go faster, its noted in the logs as 'the most productive kitchen in the world is catching up to all the orders, we need to go faster', and that's our current workflow.\""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "The principle",
      "uuid": "d885d5c20b1c43f2b51597b10c797981",
      "x": -989.600854524229,
      "y": 3069.6833474693417,
      "width": 154.0,
      "height": 29.0,
      "z_value": -9.916000000000047,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "The principle",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "User's logged kitchen metaphor",
      "uuid": "93bb263bba6c46cfab4f510ddef5f486",
      "x": -219.79983641017395,
      "y": 2707.6854267776707,
      "width": 318.0,
      "height": 29.0,
      "z_value": -9.914000000000048,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "User's logged kitchen metaphor",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Tool capability changes are ambition triggers",
      "uuid": "45ec62a6a06d4d038ccfbd99644c05ac",
      "x": -723.726357845522,
      "y": 2854.774187626688,
      "width": 468.0,
      "height": 161.0,
      "z_value": -9.915000000000047,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "  Not relaxation triggers. When the working pipeline gets faster \u2014 better model, better infrastructure, better feedback loop \u2014 the right response is to expand what gets attempted, not to do the previous workload more comfortably. The focal list is the conveyor-belt scale \u2014 if it empties, the throughput exceeded the ambition; the answer is to raise ambition, not to celebrate the catch-up."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "How to apply",
      "uuid": "9771c62270944ee3bb73d2858b9632b8",
      "x": 19.72630668790346,
      "y": 2243.894937298139,
      "width": 144.0,
      "height": 29.0,
      "z_value": -9.91100000000005,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "How to apply",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "The empty-list day during Opus 4.7's debut wasn't framed as",
      "uuid": "909d31803e6a400d863ed405848abd8c",
      "x": -32.911489919196384,
      "y": 2311.9217869427957,
      "width": 603.0,
      "height": 116.0,
      "z_value": -9.912000000000049,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "  \"We did it\" \u2014 it was framed as \"we're outrunning our own ambition, recalibrate.\" A backlog dive followed, ambition expanded, throughput climbed back to \"list always populated.\" That's the operating state."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "Connects to",
      "uuid": "ca0cd9319e234ee087aac15d4369da10",
      "x": 435.78184781533326,
      "y": 1646.6630183283933,
      "width": 134.0,
      "height": 29.0,
      "z_value": -9.90900000000005,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "Connects to",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Don't propose \"let's slow down\" after a productive stretch",
      "uuid": "38fd1a34b3294f40accdb4f1aadbe3b4",
      "x": 197.5775120638566,
      "y": 1843.1972080663038,
      "width": 594.0,
      "height": 296.0,
      "z_value": -9.91000000000005,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "  The right framing is \"what's the next harder thing.\" Productivity gains are inputs to ambition, not outputs to relax into.\n- When a model upgrade lands (or any tool/infra step-up): expect the user to want a harder problem next, not the same problem with more breathing room. The next item from the focal list will tend to be more substantial, not less.\n- Empty-focal-list moments are diagnostic, not celebratory. If we ever ship the focal list to empty in a session, the appropriate response is \"we're clearly running ahead of the backlog feed; what's the next ambition tier?\" \u2014 not \"great work, take the rest of the day off.\"\n- Feedback-loop speed compounds. The tighter our turn-around (this conversation, the proofreader, the 25M-token throughput), the faster the user can spec, build, and revise. Each capability boost multiplies through that loop.\n- \"Disorder is a trauma symptom\" \u2014 empty lists, idle periods, drift. The user's stance is that a healthy working state has the focal list always populated and turning over. The Hansen-ball mission justifies that intensity; the proactive-procrastination memory describes how rest fits in (chosen, from ahead, not from drift)."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "- feedback_perf_as_expressive_budget: the",
      "uuid": "f9abcfe8740b4d76a9ed6f85d81e624a",
      "x": -82.7074040600034,
      "y": 1519.5466505486331,
      "width": 429.0,
      "height": 221.0,
      "z_value": -9.908000000000051,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "  Optimize-first-spend-later workflow. Same idea at the model level: better capability gets spent on bigger ambition, not on the same ambition at lower load. - feedback_raise_the_ceiling \u2014 capability boosts raise the ceiling; the kitchen metaphor is the calibration mechanism for what happens once the ceiling is up. - feedback_proactive_procrastination \u2014 chosen rest is fine; drift is the failure mode. The \"list never runs empty unless something is off\" rule is the same principle on the system level. - project_hansen_ball \u2014 the underlying why. The 30k-page work demands a kitchen running flat-out; capability gains directly enable bigger creative spend on the writing."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "Note",
      "uuid": "b347c9691df04c78aa03ed9eda66b808",
      "x": 322.1128963940637,
      "y": 1390.209005310924,
      "width": 67.0,
      "height": 29.0,
      "z_value": -9.907000000000052,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "Note",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "The Opus 4.6 \u2192 4.7 transition produced a measurable",
      "uuid": "7d20480de3094f809b6378bb5a10ce1e",
      "x": 605.8099495411383,
      "y": 1303.9301439928063,
      "width": 533.0,
      "height": 161.0,
      "z_value": -9.906000000000052,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "  Workflow-shape change for this user (focal list emptying twice in one day, requiring backlog recalibration). They flagged the next model upgrade as something they're looking forward to in the same spirit \u2014 better tools = bigger ambition, not less work. The model identity isn't load-bearing; the principle is that capability and ambition stay coupled rather than ambition decoupling and relaxing as capability rises."
    }
  ],
  "connections": [
